The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | 3 farmers commit suicide
                                                                                                            3 farmers commit suicide
                            
	Akola, Feb. 6 (PTI): Three farmers have committed suicide in Maharashtra saddled by crop failure and financial burden.        
	Two of the suicides, reported since yesterday, were in Buldana district and one in Akola, police said today.        
	Gopal Ukarda Wadatkar, 60, a resident of Sawra village in Akola, set himself afire yesterday. The farmer, who owned six acres of agricultural land, was fed up with repeated crop failure and increasing burden of loan.        
	Gopals eldest son also committed suicide about four years ago, the police added.        
	Kashiram Shamrao Khodke, 38, of Kinhi Mahadeo village and Ramdas Mitharam Bharambe, 70, of Machindrakhed, both from Buldana district, hanged themselves yesterday, they said.                                                                                                                                                                           
